Hugging Face token setup (required for speaker diarization)
===========================================================

pyannote's diarization models are gated on Hugging Face, so the tool needs a
free HF access token. Provide it in EITHER of these ways — both are git-ignored
and never committed:

  Option A — environment variable (recommended):
      export HF_TOKEN=hf_your_token_here
      source env.sh

  Option B — token file:
      cp .hf_token.example .hf_token   # then edit .hf_token to contain ONLY the token
      # env.sh will read it automatically

To get a token:
  1. Create a free account at https://huggingface.co
  2. Make a token (type: Read) at https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens
  3. Accept the model terms (click "Agree") on:
       https://huggingface.co/pyannote/segmentation-3.0
       https://huggingface.co/pyannote/wespeaker-voxceleb-resnet34-LM
     (and optionally https://huggingface.co/pyannote/speaker-diarization-3.1)

Never commit your real token. If one is ever exposed, rotate it at
https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens
